name: Through The Eyes Of The Forest

metadata.name: Foxy Eyes
metadata.description:
During warm summer evenings, many critters of the forest stir, foreboding the transition to night, from day. 

As the light starts to fade, the red fox makes his appearance, being mostly nocturnal, darkness brings cover and shrouds his opportunistic ways. 

With a peering gaze, his sight reacts to movement completely without faze, locked on to his subject, it is uncommon to stray. 

Enchanted in this moment, the fox makes his move, before you know it, youâ€™ve nothing to lose.
